RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 1 5F Dirt CR: 47. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BYE BYE BIG BABY was hustled up the rail to press the pace, took the lead at the three eighths pole and flattened out in the stretch but was able to hold on. WISTFULLY was off the pace in the two path then made a late rail bid in the stretch and held on for the place. SWEETHEART VISION had no early speed then made a four to five wide late rally in the stretch. SWAMP ROCK had good early speed away from the gate then vied for the lead to the top of the stretch and gave way. DON'T BLINK TWICE raced near the back to the turn then showed late interest to improve her position. GOTTEMINABIND bobbled at the start then settled in the middle of the pack to the turn then moved out to three or four wide but failed to menace. MUCHO MACHO BABY tracked the leaders from the three path to the top of the stretch but lacked a late response. CIRCLEOFSOUL saved ground to no avail. MISS GRAND SLAM showed little.

ENTRY.NAME: Gotteminabind
ENTRY.COMMENT: bobbled start, middle of pack, no menace

ENTRY.NAME: Don't Blink Twice
ENTRY.COMMENT: near back, late interest, improved position

ENTRY.NAME: Bye Bye Big Baby
ENTRY.COMMENT: hustled up rail, led 3/8p, held on

ENTRY.NAME: Sweetheart Vision
ENTRY.COMMENT: no early speed, 4-5w stretch, late rally

ENTRY.NAME: Swamp Rock
ENTRY.COMMENT: good early speed, vied, gave way,

ENTRY.NAME: Wistfully
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, late rail bid, held second

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 2 5F Dirt CR: 96. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 27000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $7,500 OR LESS IN 2021 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $15,000. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 22 Allowed 3 lbs. A Race Since December 22 Allowed 6 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000 (Claiming Races For $7,500 Or Less Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRIZELESS stalked the pace from the two path then engaged the leader at the eighth pole and matched strides down the stretch but was able to edge away late. COROT dueled for the lead to the three eighths pole, took a clear lead to the top of the stretch was headed and fought down the stretch to be a game second. PICKENS tracked the leaders from the three path to the top of the stretch moved back to the inside and slipped through at the sixteenths pole to be up for show. COLONEL KLINK had no early speed then moved out to three or four wide in upper stretch to finish strong. INDIA INK was off the pace on the inside but failed to menace. BEVERLY PARK was not a threat. CRIMSON STORM had a mild bid on the turn and weakened. CREEKMORE dueled for the lead from the two path to the three eighths pole and gave way grudgingly.

ENTRY.NAME: Prizeless
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked pace, engaged 1/8p, edged away late

ENTRY.NAME: Creekmore
ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled for lead, gave way grudgingly

ENTRY.NAME: Pickens
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked leaders, slipped through, up show

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 3 1M Dirt CR: 54. Maiden Claiming Purse 18000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WHEELS TURNING stalked the pace down the backstretch then started his bid at the three eighths pole and took command nearing the quarter pole and drew away. R T'S IRON MAN saved ground throughout, then had a stretch duel inside of PLAY MASTER and won the nod for the place. PLAY MASTER raced in the middle of the pack then moved out four wide at the quarter pole, had a stretch duel outside of RT'S IRON MAN but was out nodded for the place. KATS PICK raced near the back down the backstretch, ran into traffic on the final turn then moved out to three or four wide in upper stretch for a late rally. BOSS MAN ZONG tracked the leaders to the final turn and retreated. SNAKEBIT raced in the middle of the pack, made a three wide bid at the quarter pole but failed to menace. INDEFENSIBLE TOWN was not a threat. HE'S A CLASSIC shot to a clear lead to the three eighths pole and stopped.

ENTRY.NAME: Play Master
ENTRY.COMMENT: middle of pack, 4w1/4p, stretch duel, outnodded

ENTRY.NAME: Snakebit
ENTRY.COMMENT: middle of pack, 3w1/4p, failed to menace,

ENTRY.NAME: R T's Iron Man
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, dueled stretch, won nod 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Kats Pick
ENTRY.COMMENT: back, traffic 2nd turn, 3-4w upper, late rally

ENTRY.NAME: Wheels Turning
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked pace, bid 3/8p, took command, drew clear,

Non-winners Of A Race Since January 22 Allowed 3 lbs. A Race Since December 22 Allowed 6 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Condition Eligibility Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOT CAROL vied for the lead to the top of the stretch then took over and drew clear. THINKITASADONATION tracked the leaders from the two path then made a late surge in the final sixteenth but was not enough. MYSTERIOUS STAR had good speed while being challenged and gave way grudgingly. BITSY C C LIL GIRL raced in the middle of the pack down the backstretch then made a three wide bid on the turn and flattened out. ALYS EPISODE was off the pace on the inside while racing evenly. CUSTOM GUITAR raced in the middle of the pack but failed to menace. COLD AS YOU was not a threat. ANGEL ARKIE broke out slightly, went three or four wide on the turn but was never a factor. FORT PIKE was outrun.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 5 7 1/2F Dirt CR: 75. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 22 Allowed 3 lbs. A Race Since December 22 Allowed 6 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Claiming Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Estima ting Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FRIENDOFTHECOURT pressed the pace to the first turn then took a clear lead on the backstretch and won going away. TAPPED OUT had good speed to take the early challenged lead to the first turn then vied for the lead to the final turn and weakened but made a rebid to save the place. WEDINGTON was forwardly placed around the first turn then made a three wide middle move but was out finished in late stretch. DALLAS GOLD was taken up to avoid the loose rival at the start then was allowed to settle around the first turn and made a rebid three wide at the quarter pole and just missed the show. BODE'S LIGHT raced near the back down the backstretch then made a three wide bid at the five sixteenths pole to improve position. SECULAR STAGNATION was allowed to settle to the final turn then made a three wide bid a the three sixteenths pole but failed to menace. WAYPOINT was off the pace on the inside but was not a threat. LIAM SKYE was always back. DEALMEINBUD was off the pace down the backstretch and retreated. BIG ROJO stumbled badly at the start, lost his rider and walked off. STEWARDS INQUIRY INTO THE START OF THE RACE, AFTER A REVIEW STEWARDS DECLARED THAT BIG ROJO WAS THE CAUSE OF HIS OWN PROBLEMS SO THERE WAS NO CHANGES. FINAL TIME WAS ADJUSTED FROM 134.59 TO 135.52.

ENTRY.COMMENT: stumbled badly, lost rider, walked off

ENTRY.COMMENT: avoid loose horse, allowed to settle, rebid, missed show

ENTRY.COMMENT: allowed to settle, 3w3/16p, failed to menace,

ENTRY.COMMENT: challenged lead, vied for lead, weakened, saved 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Friendofthecourt
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace, clear lead, going away

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 6 5F Dirt CR: 72. Allowance Purse 43000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER OR TRIAL OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 22 Allowed 3 lbs. A Race Since December 22 Allowed 6 lbs. (Claiming Races Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISS PRIORITY shot to the lead to set the pace, was headed at the top of the stretch, fought off all challengers and held on. DEAL ME A PENNY tracked the leaders down the backstretch launched a three or four wide bid a the five sixteenths pole, moving out to five wide in upper stretch for the late run but was too late. ZEATRICAL pressed the pace from the three path then engaged leader at the eighth pole and fought gamely to the wire. CHARGED TEMP raced in the middle of the pack to the turn then made a two wide bid, moved back inside in the stretch drive and finished evenly. BUILDING HOME vied for the lead from the four path then engaged the leader at the top of the stretch and fought gamely to deep stretch and weakened. BRAVE OLLIE was off the pace on the inside and failed to menace. SHEZA SALTY GAL raced in the middle of the pace from the inside but was not a factor. STORM BREACH had no speed and was not a threat. ENVOYS LEGACY was always back. BETISON vied for the lead from the two path to the three eighths and dropped back.

ENTRY.NAME: Charged Temp
ENTRY.COMMENT: middle of pack, 2wturn, inside stretch, finished evenly

ENTRY.NAME: Miss Priority
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace, fought gamely, held on

ENTRY.NAME: Zeatrical
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace, engaged leader, fought gamely

ENTRY.NAME: Deal Me a Penny
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked leaders, 3-4w5/16p, 5wupper, late run, too late

ENTRY.NAME: Building Home
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied for lead, engaged leader, gamely, weakened,

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 7 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 51. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since January 22 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000. Louisiana Bred Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ST MARIA went to a challenged lead to the three eighths then inched away, drew clear on the turn and was ridden out. MISS MIRACLE GIRL pressed the pace from the two path to the three eighths pole and was no match for the winner but was a clear second. SARATOGA KAREN stalked the pace from the inside and passed tiring rival. OVERLY SWEET was unhurried down the backstretch then made a three wide bid on the final turn, moving out to five wide in upper stretch and made a late rally. VANCOUVER SNOW was allowed to settle around the first turn then made a three wide bid at the three eighths and flattened out. TALE OF TENSAS was forwardly placed in the three path to the top of the stretch and gave way. I LOVE YOU MORE tracked the leaders around the first turn and retreated. GALAXY AFFAIR chased the leaders around the first turn and dropped back.

ENTRY.NAME: St Maria
ENTRY.COMMENT: challenged lead, drew clear, ridden out

ENTRY.NAME: Miss Miracle Girl
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace, no match, clear second

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 8 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 76. Allowance Purse 43000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED THREE YEAR OLDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 120 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 22 Allowed 3 lbs. (Claiming Races Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOR BIG LEE was unsettled in the gate, tracked the leaders around the first turn then moved up on the backstretch, making his bid at the three eighths pole from four wide then took the lead at the five sixteenths pole and just lasted. I SEE CLEARLY NOW pressed the pace from the inside to the final turn then dropped back, made a rebid up the rail into the stretch and just missed. RANCH WATER was allowed to settle down the backstretch then made a three or four wide at the five sixteenths pole for a late rally and missed the place. KAJUN KARMA was restless in the gate, unhurried down the backstretch then moved up on the final turn, going four to five wide in upper stretch for a late run but only passed tiring rivals. GOLDENLUTE had good early speed around the first turn then vied for the lead down the backstretch, dueled around the final turn and shook loose but weakened. A MILLION STARS failed to menace. MAKE YOUR DESTINY saved ground to no avail. FLASHY BOY went five wide into the first turn the vied for the lead to the quarter pole and gave way. CARLOS'S MAMA was never a threat. ADIEU ACES was loose in the post parade, was forwardly placed around the first turn then moved up from five wide at the three eighths pole, when asked entering the turn he stopped, distanced, jogged in, walked off.

ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace, dropped back, rebid, just missed

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 9 5F Dirt CR: 66. Maiden Special Weight Purse 34000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For Less Than $20,000 In Their Last Three Starts).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MY AUNT SNOOKIE was hustled to the lead from the inside then pulled away at the three eighths pole and was ridden out to prove much the best. LUMINOUS FLIGHT was off the pace in the two path then moved out to three wide at the three sixteenths pole to be a clear second. BLACK ACE was off the pace in the four path then move in slightly at the three sixteenths pole but was out finished. ALABAMA QUEEN raced in the middle of the pack down the backstretch then made a two wide bid on the turn, moved in to slip up the rail but finished evenly. LEPRECHAUN CHARM was off the pace in the three path then moved out to four wide at the three sixteenths pole to show late interest. SASSY SPRY raced near the back on the backstretch then made a three wide bid at the quarter pole, moved between horses at the sixteenths pole to improve position. BOTTLES AN BIBLES had no early speed and was never a serious threat. HIDDEN LOVE pressed the pace from the two path to the three eighths pole and weakened. MDA RUN ADDRESS was forwardly placed on the inside early but was not a factor. LYRICAL MUSIC vied for the lead from the three path to the five sixteenths pole and gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Alabama Queen
ENTRY.COMMENT: middle of pack, 2wturn, slip up rail, evenly

ENTRY.NAME: My Aunt Snookie
ENTRY.COMMENT: hustled to lead, pulled away, ridden out, much the best
